# Organization Tenant Ownership

Authoritative contract: `docs/platforms/backend/contracts/organization-domain.md`.

## ORM

- `Organization` is a **non-actor** model.
- Own via `customer_id` → `Customer.id` with a **real FK** (no `constraints: false`).
- Enforce **one org per customer** with a unique index on `customer_id`.
- Do not remodel this as polymorphic `owner_type` / `owner_id` unless product ownership changes.
- On `Customer`: keep `hasOne(Organization)` + mixins `getOrganization` / `setOrganization` / `createOrganization`; do not move tenant identity fields onto Customer attrs.

## Attrs layout

Group Attrs comments as `//relations`, `//info`, `//virtual` and keep `attributes()` field order aligned.

## Customer GQL root-one

For customer-role `organization` when `Customer.hasOne(Organization)` uses association key `organization` matching bridge `ident`:

- Resolver: `prepareOneGQLModel({ me: true })`
- Bridge stays minimal (`ident` / `typeIdent` / `ormModel` + typed `{ me: true }` parent)
- Do **not** add `as` or override `getRootOrmParent` / `getOrmFindOptions` unless the association key differs or default accessor scoping is insufficient

## Supervisor GQL

- List/detail roots live on supervisor schema; nested `_Customer.organization` requires `OrganizationBridge` registered.
- Keep list queries bounded (`withListable`) and deterministically ordered.
- Do not sync supervisor organization mirrors into `cpanel/` while that platform checkout is absent; website customer mirrors remain the only active frontend sync for this domain.

## Members (related)

- `Member` belongs to Organization; see `docs/platforms/backend/contracts/member-domain.md`.
- Customer GQL: root `members` / `member(id)` only — not nested `_Organization.members` (B15).
- Inverse `_Member.organization` requires `OrganizationBridge` `GetOneParent` to include `MemberModel`.

## Message templates (related)

- `MessageTemplate` belongs to Organization; see `docs/platforms/backend/contracts/message-template-domain.md`.
- Customer GQL: root `messageTemplates` / `messageTemplate(id)` — not nested under `_Organization`.
- Inverse `_MessageTemplate.organization` requires `OrganizationBridge` `GetOneParent` to include `MessageTemplateModel`.
- Org-owned customer bridges extend `CustomerOrganizationOwnedBridgeBase` for `{ me: true }` → Organization.
